abstract: A leading Israeli opposition figure said Monday that embattled Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has turned a U.S. initiative for ending conflict with the Palestinians into a campaign “stunt” by pushing for the immediate annexation of West Bank settlements.
snippet: A leading Israeli opposition figure said Monday that embattled Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has turned a U.S. initiative for ending conflict with the Palestinians into a campaign “stunt” by pushing for the immediate annexation of West...
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — A leading Israeli opposition figure said Monday that embattled Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has turned a U.S. initiative for ending conflict with the Palestinians into a campaign “stunt” by pushing for the immediate annexation of West Bank settlements.
headline_main: Israeli Opposition Co-Leader: PM Makes Trump Plan a 'Stunt'
headline_print_headline: Israeli Opposition Co-Leader: PM Makes Trump Plan a 'Stunt'

abstract: The budget predicts the economy will grow significantly faster than most economists anticipate.
snippet: The budget predicts the economy will grow significantly faster than most economists anticipate.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s budget proposals have been defined by a belief that the economy will grow significantly faster than most economists anticipate. The latest version, released on Monday, is a brief departure: It concedes, for the first time, that the administration’s past projections were too optimistic.

abstract: A high-profile North Korean defector said Tuesday he’ll run in upcoming parliamentary elections in South Korea as part of his efforts to help South Koreans understand the true nature of North Korea and map out a better unification policy.
snippet: A high-profile North Korean defector said Tuesday he’ll run in upcoming parliamentary elections in South Korea as part of his efforts to help South Koreans understand the true nature of North Korea and map out a better unification policy.
lead_paragraph: SEOUL, South Korea — A high-profile North Korean defector said Tuesday he’ll run in upcoming parliamentary elections in South Korea as part of his efforts to help South Koreans understand the true nature of North Korea and map out a better unification policy.
headline_main: High-Level North Defector to Run for South Korean Parliament
headline_print_headline: High-Level North Defector to Run for South Korean Parliament

abstract: NATO's public image in the United States and France worsened sharply last year, according to a Pew Research Center study, after U.S. President Donald Trump and French President Emmanuel Macron questioned the value of the Western alliance.
snippet: NATO's public image in the United States and France worsened sharply last year, according to a Pew Research Center study, after U.S. President Donald Trump and French President Emmanuel Macron questioned the value of the Western alliance.
lead_paragraph: BRUSSELS — NATO's public image in the United States and France worsened sharply last year, according to a Pew Research Center study, after U.S. President Donald Trump and French President Emmanuel Macron questioned the value of the Western alliance.
headline_main: NATO's Image Worsens Sharply in France, United States, Study Shows
headline_print_headline: NATO's Image Worsens Sharply in France, United States, Study Shows

abstract: The investor Chamath Palihapitiya urged start-ups and venture capitalists to reconsider where they get their money from, in light of a new report on a Mormon Church mega-fund.
snippet: The investor Chamath Palihapitiya urged start-ups and venture capitalists to reconsider where they get their money from, in light of a new report on a Mormon Church mega-fund.

abstract: A New Hampshire family that received a $1,000-a-month "freedom dividend" for a year from the campaign of Democratic presidential contender Andrew Yang spent most of the money on college bills - but also on an improv class for the unemployed dad.
snippet: A New Hampshire family that received a $1,000-a-month "freedom dividend" for a year from the campaign of Democratic presidential contender Andrew Yang spent most of the money on college bills - but also on an improv class for the unemployed dad.
lead_paragraph: GOFFSTOWN, N.H. — A New Hampshire family that received a $1,000-a-month "freedom dividend" for a year from the campaign of Democratic presidential contender Andrew Yang spent most of the money on college bills - but also on an improv class for the unemployed dad.
headline_main: How a New Hampshire Family Spent Andrew Yang's 'Freedom Dividend'
headline_print_headline: How a New Hampshire Family Spent Andrew Yang's 'Freedom Dividend'

abstract: President Donald Trump's $4.8 trillion budget plan for the coming fiscal year drew a prompt rejection on Monday from congressional Democrats, who said it betrayed his promise to protect popular health and safety-net programs.
snippet: President Donald Trump's $4.8 trillion budget plan for the coming fiscal year drew a prompt rejection on Monday from congressional Democrats, who said it betrayed his promise to protect popular health and safety-net programs.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump's $4.8 trillion budget plan for the coming fiscal year drew a prompt rejection on Monday from congressional Democrats, who said it betrayed his promise to protect popular health and safety-net programs.
headline_main: Trump's $4.8 Trillion Budget Gets Chilly Reception From Congress
headline_print_headline: Trump's $4.8 Trillion Budget Gets Chilly Reception From Congress

abstract: A day before New Hampshire votes in its Democratic presidential primary, Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg sought on Monday to build on their strength as front-runners in an up-for-grabs race as an energized Senator Amy Klobuchar gained ground.
snippet: A day before New Hampshire votes in its Democratic presidential primary, Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg sought on Monday to build on their strength as front-runners in an up-for-grabs race as an energized Senator Amy Klobuchar gained ground....
lead_paragraph: KEENE/NASHUA, N.H. — A day before New Hampshire votes in its Democratic presidential primary, Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg sought on Monday to build on their strength as front-runners in an up-for-grabs race as an energized Senator Amy Klobuchar gained ground.
headline_main: On Eve of New Hampshire Democratic Vote, Klobuchar Gains Ground on Sanders and Buttigieg
headline_print_headline: On Eve of New Hampshire Democratic Vote, Klobuchar Gains Ground on Sanders and Buttigieg

abstract: For the past year, Democratic voters have been anxious to settle on a savior capable of defeating President Donald Trump.
